\begin_layout Standard
Although empirical studies have shed light on the global economic costs
 of natural disasters, precisely studying the characteristics of these costs
 remains challenging.
 One of the primary difficulties arises from the inherently indirect nature
 of the effects identified by models, making it problematic to isolate them
 in empirical data 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
